<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" Runat="Server">
    <h1>
        SE Boards Help
    </h1>
    <div class="about_us_pages">
        <p>
            To view all jobs posted on the site:
            <br />
            Return to the home page, select your desired filter options from the menu on the right, and browse all our listed jobs.
        </p>
        <p>
            To create a job seeker account:
            <br />
            Visit our login page through the navigation menu and follow the new account link within the login pageor click the new 
            account link in the footer. Once on the new account page, fill out the form making sure to select job seeker from the 
            drop down list and you will be registered on the site as a job seeker.
        </p>
        <p>
            To create an employer account
            <br />
            Visit our login page through the navigation menu and follow the new account link within the login pageor click the new 
            account link in the footer. Once on the new account page, fill out the form making sure to select employer from the 
            drop down list and you will be registered on the site as an employer.
        </p>
        <p>
            To create a job posting
            <br />
            Create an employer account, log into your employer account, visit the employer page using either the navigation menu or
            footer links and click the add job posting link. Fill out the form and your job will be added to the list of jobs on our site.
        </p>
    </div>
